 General Forms:
 (fancy-use lmi+)
 (fancy-use lmi+ thy)
 (fancy-use lmi+ thy alt-thy)
 (fancy-use lmi+ thy alt-thy verbose)
 })

 <p>where @('lmi+') is a @(see lemma-instance) or a true list of
 lemma-instances, that is, an object that can be supplied as a @(':use') hint
